Metso Wins 20 Million Euro Contract to Build Biomass Power Plant

-- B y   K a t i e   L i n s e l l
-- 
2011-08-10T15:34:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/metso-wins-20-million-euro-contract-to-build-biomass-power-plant.html
Metso Oyj, a Finnish producer of
paper machines and rock crushers, won a 20 million euro ($28.4
million) deal to build a biomass power plant in east  Germany .  The plant will burn waste wood to produce 10 megawatts of
heat and 5 megawatts of electricity for the municipality of
Zwickau, and connect to the grid in late 2012, Helsinki-based
Metso said today in a  statement on its website .  MW Power, a joint venture between Metso and Wartsila Oyj,
will build the plant, its eighth combined heat and power site in
Germany. The venture has also set up facilities in Finland,
Sweden, Belgium, the  Czech Republic , Belarus and Ireland.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katie Linsell in London at 
